videos.headline: Cook scores on Seminoles' opening drive
videos.description: Dalvin Cook averaging 10 yards a carry on the opening drive, scores a two-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: Peppers out of Orange Bowl with hamstring injury
videos.description: Steve Levy and Brian Griese discuss Jabrill Peppers being ruled out of the Capital One Orange Bowl and how it impacts Michigan's defense against Florida State.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF News (Peppers out of Orange Bowl with hamstring injury) 2016/12/30

videos.headline: Nyqwan Murray muffs the Kenny Allen punt, Michigan recovers
videos.description: Kenny Allen's booming punt is muffed by Nyqwan Murray. Michigan recovers the ball at the one-yard line.

videos.headline: Dalvin Cook hauls in 45-yard pass
videos.description: On the first play of the 2nd drive, Dalvin Cook gets free for a 45-yard pass reception.

videos.headline: Francois takes big hit
videos.description: Taco Charlton hit on Deondre Francois sends him to the ground. He would be taken out of the game, but later return.

videos.headline: Francois connects with Murray for a 92-yard TD
videos.description: Deondre Francois throws the deep ball to Nyqwan Murray for 92 yards, an Orange Bowl record for longest touchdown, and the Seminoles go up 17-3.

videos.headline: FSU horse Renegade falls before spear toss, he would be ok
videos.description: Florida State's Horse Renegade loses his balanance and falls before Chief Osceaola throws the spear onto the field in pregame for the Seminoles' game against Michigan. Renegade would quickly return to his feet.

videos.headline: Marshall gets penalty for late hit
videos.description: Trey Marshall hits Eddie McDoom late and costs Florida State 15 extra yards.

videos.headline: Jake Butt goes down with leg injury
videos.description: After a 16-yard reception, Jake Butt takes a hit, suffers a leg injury and has to leave the game.

videos.headline: Michigan shows long-I formation again
videos.description: Michigan shows its single-lined I formation, but the play is shut down by Florida State's defense in the second quarter.

videos.headline: Michigan called for pass interference.
videos.description: Florida State's Keith Gavin draws a free 15 yards, on a defensive pass interference call by Michigan's Lavert Hill.

videos.headline: Francois connects with Murray for a 92-yard TD
videos.description: Deondre Francois throws the deep ball to Nyqwan Murray for 92 yards, an Orange Bowl record for longest touchdown, and the Seminoles go up 17-3.

tracking.trackingName: NCB-One-Play (Francois connects with Murray for a 92-yard TD) 2016/12/30 ESHEET

videos.headline: Michigan converts 4th down on the 1st drive of the 2nd half
videos.description: Wilton Speight finds Ian Bunting for 21 yards as Michigan converts the 4th down on opening drive of the 2nd half.

videos.headline: De'Veon Smith hurdles a Florida State player
videos.description: De'Veon Smith on his way to a 13-yard run, hurdles over a Florida State player.

videos.headline: Michigan denied in the Red Zone again
videos.description: Wilton Speight is sacked by Josh Sweat on 3rd down to force another Michigan field goal attempt.

videos.headline: McCray's pick-six gets Michigan first TD
videos.description: Deondre Francis is intercepted by Mike McCray, who then returns the ball to the end zone for a touchdown.

videos.headline: Maurice Hurst sacks Deondre Francois
videos.description: Deondre Francois is sacked by Maurice Hurst to create 3rd and 22

videos.headline: Cook flips the field on a 71-yard run
videos.description: Dalvin Cook takes off 71 yards before getting pushed out, setting Florida State up for a touchdown.

videos.headline: Francois responds with a three-yard TD for FSU
videos.description: Deondre Francois calls his own number on the option to score the touchdown and put Florida State up 27-15.

videos.headline: Demarcus Walker forces a Michigan punt with a sack
videos.description: Wilton Speight is sacked by Demarcus Walker to force another Michigan punt.

videos.headline: Trey Marshall is ejected for targeting
videos.description: FSU's Trey Marshall is ejected for targeting after hitting Jourdan Lewis in the helmet.

videos.headline: Speight connects with Hill for first Michigan offensive TD
videos.description: Wilton Speight's eight-yard TD pass to Khalid Hill brings the Wolverines within one score of the Seminoles.

videos.headline: Evans runs in for 30-yard score
videos.description: Chris Evans' 30-yard TD run gives Michigan its first lead with under two minutes left in the game.

videos.headline: Keith Gavin returns kickoff 66 yards
videos.description: Keith Gavin's 66-yard kickoff return sets up the Seminoles in Michigan territory.

videos.headline: Murray's second TD lifts FSU to Orange Bowl win
videos.description: Nyqwan Murray's 12-yard touchdown reception puts FSU ahead 33-30 with under a minute left in the game

videos.headline: Michigan blocks the PAT and returns it for 2 points
videos.description: Josh Metellus returns the blocked PAT for two points, and Michigan is down just one with under a minute left.

videos.headline: Carlos Becker's INT seals the game for FSU
videos.description: Carlos Becker intercepts the Wilton Speight pass to seal the Capitol One Orange Bowl for Florida State.

videos.headline: Orange Bowl wins says a lot about character of FSU
videos.description: Kirk Herbstreit breaks down the last 15 minutes of the Capital One Orange Bowl, with Michigan hanging in the game and Florida State staying composed to pull out the victory.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Analysis (Orange Bowl wins says a lot about character of FSU) 2016/12/30 SVP SC ESHEET

videos.headline: Matich says Michigan 'will see this as a missed opportunity'
videos.description: Despite making forward progress to Michigan's program, Trevor Matich explains how the seniors on the Wolverines will look back on this season as a loss.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Analysis (Matich says Michigan 'will see this as a missed opportunity') 2016/12/30 SC

videos.headline: Vilma continues to stay impressed by Walker
videos.description: Jonathan Vilma discusses DeMarcus Walker's tremendous performance by becoming the leader for Florida State's defense and making the necessary plays to defeat Michigan.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Analysis (Vilma continues to stay impressed by Walker) 2016/12/30 ESHEET SC

videos.headline: Florida State prevails to stop Michigan in Orange Bowl
videos.description: Florida State withstands a thrilling Michigan comeback with Dalvin Cook totaling 207 yards and Deondre Francois teaming up with Nyqwan Murray for the winning touchdown in a 33-32 Capital One Orange Bowl victory.
